the movie gives us very little reason to think that the fivedimensional beings are future humans that possibility was completely baseless speculation by cooper there is no evidence whatsoever in the story that he is correct even if the wormhole builders are future humans we dont have a paradox if the eternalist view of time is correct and the movie clearly presumes that eternalism is indeed correct the future humans saving the present humans so that the present humans live long enough to become the future humans is an example of circular causality a causes b then b causes a then a causes b then b causes a and so on the thing is viewed from a fiveplus dimensional perspective the past the present and the future as we call them are all equally real and equally accessible from the fifth dimension event a and event b are basically simultaneous and are both visible on the time curve and here is the real important part there is no version of the time curve in which a and b do not exist no version of the time curve in which a does not cause b and no version in which b does not cause a there is no first play through in which the future did not yet exist to interact with the past according to eternalism the future and the past always exist are always just as real as the present and for five dimensional beings the unchanging past and the unchanging future are just as accessible as the present most scientists say that causality does not work like that and time travel is not possible a minority of scientists say causality does work like this and time travel is possible as long as the past is not changed obviously being a time travel story the movie went with the second explanation in short it might be a mind screw but it is not necessarily a paradox and while there are at least a dozen serious plot holes in this movie the way time travel is handled isnt one of them

present and the future as we call them are all equally real and equally accessible from the fifth dimension event a and event b are basically simultaneous and are both visible on the time curve and here is the real important part there is no version of the time curve in which a and b do not exist no version of the time curve in which a does not cause b and no version in which b does not cause a there is no first play through in which the future did not yet exist to interact with the past according to eternalism the future and the past always exist are always just as real as the present and the movie gives us very little reason to think that the fivedimensional beings are future humans that possibility was completely baseless speculation by cooper there is no evidence whatsoever in the story that he is correct even if the wormhole builders are future humans we dont have a paradox if the eternalist view of time is correct and the movie clearly presumes that eternalism is indeed correct the future humans saving the present humans so that the present humans live long enough to become the future humans is an example of circular causality a causes b then b causes a then a causes b then b causes a and so on the thing is viewed from a fiveplus dimensional perspective the past the present and the future as we call them are all equally real and equally accessible from the fifth dimension event a and event b are basically simultaneous and are both visible on the time curve and here is the real important part there is no version of the time curve in which a and b do not exist no version of the time curve in which a does not cause b and no version in which b does not cause a there is no first play through in which the future did not yet exist to interact with the past according to eternalism the future and the past always exist are always just as real as the present and for five dimensional beings the unchanging past and the unchanging future are just as accessible as the present most scientists say that causality does not work like that and time travel is not possible a minority of scientists say causality does work like this and time travel is possible as long as the past is not changed obviously being a time travel story the movie went with the second explanation in short it might be a mind screw but it is not necessarily a paradox and while there are at least a dozen serious plot holes in this movie the way time travel is handled isnt one of them

here is a comment of mine from another interstellar vid im going to play a little devils advocate and say that cooper didnt survive the blackhole and that gravity did tear him apart one can argue that the wormhole wasnt placed there by them that it was just a naturallyoccurring phenomenon once cooper travels past the event horizon on the otherside of the wormhole its plausible that its his vision of the afterlife its not the future that he is experiencing but he is experiencing heaven christopher nolan plays on this idea of love and certain religious symbolism throughout the entirety of the film therefore you could argue that what is being presented as the future of humanity in the film is coopers view of the afterlife since he is experiencing heaven this is why he sees baseball being played his house is there and finally sees murph new members of his family these things may not be certain bits of the future but memories interwoven into his afterlife experience now do i believe my own hypothesis no but i think there is enough evidence to argue that its a plausible theory

jshaw warning lots of text to follow well that would be the unknown portion that no theory hascan explain we know humans were dangerously close to extinction in our time and we know that humans of the future graduated to a higher plane of existence but thats all we know how they attained godlike powers is anyones guess i only propose that instead of d humans being earth born which causes a huge paradox that they were space colonists i have no hypothesis for how they evolved im sure given enough time the scientific method would yield great results maybe given enough time all organisms could unlock the secrets of the cosmos and level up to dimensions above our the reasoning for my colonist hypothesis is it seems to not cause an infinite loop paradox i thought it was almost an oversight how they shoehorned a second clip at the very end of the movie showing brand in the process of colonizing her planet i felt the short clip was delivered in such a way as to hint to the possibility that cooper wasnt the only hero it not only seems to resolve the paradox but also promotes brands character to actually being central to the overall story i think it was a deliberate decision to not focus on brand after the black hole scene to make the audience forget the colonists and focus on cooper for the express purpose of a semiopen ended story this is why i love movies like this the usual suspects the thirteenth floor blade runner any kubrick film etc because they drop hints that point to one possible logical conclusion but never actually divulge the truth it sparks all kinds of great debates and ideas that live in our minds long after the end credits i liked the movie when i saw it but after contemplating possible answers to the paradox i can say i now love this movie

i think whether you liked the movie or not depends upon your understanding of physics and the relation between gravitational force and time this movie explores the theory of general relativity very well the use of gravity time dilation in the way the astronauts dont age as time becomes slower for them due to the increasing gravitational force of the planets is incredible the working of a wormhole is also beautifully and accurately shown the depiction of how a black hole looks from the outside is accurate as hell and a sight to behold the use of centrifugal force to produce g so that the astronauts can walk inside the spacecraft normally is clever the use of consevation of momentum to provide gravitational assist to the spacecraft to escape the black hole thats all real physics i was so much invested in the movie because right now im pursuing a masters degree in theoretical physics and to see a movie depict all of those complex concepts of physics so fluidly and beautifully was more than enough for making me love the movie now about the end of the movie we still dont know for sure whats inside a black hole what we do know is that black holes the rotating ones might act as some sort of teleporting devices by bending the curvature of spacetime so that could explain how he managed to reach back to our solar system however we know that a person would never be able to survive the journey to the centre of the black hole since the enormous gravitational force would squeeze him like a spaghetti but still no one hasent gone into a black hole so we dont know for sure what happens inside it thats why im fine with what they showed at the end of the film because although we dont know what will happen if we go inside a black hole it is generally accepted among physicists that whatever happens inside it its bizarre as hell nevertheless this film is a treat to watch because seeing all these complex and mysterious phenomena on the big screen and that too so accurately depicted along with the great cast realistic acting astounding visual effects mesmerising music and awesome direction is more than enough for me to call this movie a masterpiece

the idea i got from the scenes inside the black hole is this when you pass the event horizon all paths lead to the singularity at no point is it possible to get further away from the singularity or even to remain at a constant distance from it this means that the dimension of space in the direction of the singularity becomes timelike so time as experienced outside the black hole must become spacelike this means that he can move back and forth through time in the same manner he normally could through a given dimension of space at least for as long as he has before he becomes spaghettified by proximity to the singularity which is his inescapable future so the library inside the black hole to me represented universal time as a spacelike dimension in which he could move at will because his formerly spacelike path to the singularity had become his axis of time this is what enabled him to travel back in time to his daughters childhood and leave the message stay on her bookshelf before he was crushed by the singularity
